{"lemma": "بَدْء", "slug": "بَدْء", "root": "ب.د.#", "root_slug": "ب-د-_", "root_link": "/words/roots/ب-د-_", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n1952", "n1953"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%A1"}}, "translations": {"en": "beginning", "fa": "آغاز", "ur": "شروعات", "tr": "başlangıç", "id": "permulaan", "bn": "শুরু", "es": "comienzo", "fr": "commencement", "de": "Anfang", "ru": "начало", "zh": "开始"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of بَدَأَ (badaʔa) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "beginning, start", "examples": [{"text": "بَدْءًا مِنْ صَبَاحِ الْإِثْنَيْنِ", "english": "starting Monday morning"}, {"text": "مُنْذُ الْبَدْءِ", "english": "from the very beginning"}]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/badʔ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n1952", "headword_ar": "بَدءٌ", "root": "bdA^", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "inf.n. of 1; (T, S, M, Msb;) [The act of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beginning;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "doing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a thing"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "first."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laka Albado'u", "text_ar": "لَكَ البَدْءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albudo'u", "text_ar": "البُدْءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (As, TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbadoA^apu", "text_ar": "البَدْاَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, Msb, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbudoA^apu", "text_ar": "البُدْاَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbidoA^apu", "text_ar": "البِدْاَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (L,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbadaA='apu", "text_ar": "البَدَا=ءَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbudaA='apu", "text_ar": "البُدَا=ءَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbudaAhapu", "text_ar": "البُدَاهَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "substituted for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Mtr,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbidaA='apu", "text_ar": "البِدَا=ءَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mtr, TA,) and, accord. to IKtt,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbidaAyapu", "text_ar": "البِدَايَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but see what follows, (TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albadiy^apu", "text_ar": "البَدِيَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albud~aA='apu", "text_ar": "البُدَّا=ءَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (AZ, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is for thee to begin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "before any other,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in shooting or casting, &c.: (S:) as to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbidaAyapu", "text_ar": "البِدَايَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", mentioned above, accord. to Mtr [and Fei], (TA,) it is a vulgar word, (Mgh, Msb, TA,) as IB and several others have stated, (Msb, TA, *) a corruption of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbidaA='apu", "text_ar": "البِدَا=ءَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mgh, Msb,) signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the first;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbudaA='apu", "text_ar": "البُدَا=ءَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbadoA^apu", "text_ar": "البَدْاَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) but IKtt says that it is a word of the dial. of the Ansár;"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badaA^otu biAl$~aYo'i", "text_ar": "بَدَاْتُ بِالشَّىْءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiytu", "text_ar": "بَدِيتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bihi", "text_ar": "بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qad~amotuhu", "text_ar": "قَدَّمْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": [see 1:] and he cites the following verse of Ibn-Rawáhah:"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "walawo EabadonaA gayorahu $aqiynaA \n                      \n                     \n                        biA@somi A@loA_ilaAhi wa bihi badiynaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In the name of God, and with it we begin; and if we worshipped any other than Him, we should be miserable"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bdY", "text_ar": "بدى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA. [This verse is also cited in the S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bdw", "text_ar": "بدو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", where, in one copy I find it as above; in another, with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badayonaA", "text_ar": "بَدَيْنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "instead of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiyonaA", "text_ar": "بَدِيْنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) And you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEalahu Eawo*aA wabado'FA", "text_ar": "فَعَلَهُ عَوْذَا وَبَدْءًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, S,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eawodahu Ealay badoy^ihi", "text_ar": "عَوْدَهُ عَلَي بَدْيِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Eawodihi", "text_ar": "فِى عَوْدِهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wabadoy^ihi", "text_ar": "وَبَدْيِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Eawodatihi wabadoA^atihi", "text_ar": "فِى عَوْدَتِهِ وَبَدْاَتِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He did it returning and beginning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "again; or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "returning to his beginning;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he did it again from the beginning; he recommenced it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or you say this] meaning like as is meant by the saying next following. (TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajaEa Eawodahu EalaY badoy^ihi", "text_ar": "رَجَعَ عَوْدَهُ عَلَى بَدْيِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawodFA EalaY bado'K", "text_ar": "عَوْدًا عَلَى بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in both of which [and in the last following] the verb may be trans., and the noun following therefore in the accus. case, (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Eawodihi wabadoy^ihi", "text_ar": "فِى عَوْدِهِ وَبَدْيِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Eawodatihi wabadoA^atihi", "text_ar": "فِى عَوْدَتِهِ وَبَدْاَتِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [in both of which, if correct, the verb must be intrans.,] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EawodFA wabado'FA", "text_ar": "عَوْدًا وَبَدْءًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [as though meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAy^idFA wabaAdiy^FA", "text_ar": "عَايِدًا وَبَادِيًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", used as a phrase denotative of state,] (K,) [but in this last, and the two next preceding, accord. to the TA, the verb should be"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEalahu", "text_ar": "فَعَلَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in the next preceding sentence, instead of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajaEa", "text_ar": "رَجَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and this is confirmed by what is said in the K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ewd", "text_ar": "عود"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He returned in the way whence he had come:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) [accord. to the TA, the literal meaning of the first and second may be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he made his returning to revert to his beginning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he made a returning to revert to a beginning:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] or the meaning of the first, (Sb, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ewd", "text_ar": "عود"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and K in that art.,) and of the second, (K in that art.,) is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he returned without stopping after he had gone away:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Sb, K:) and sometimes it signifies the stopping in one's coming and then returning: (Sb:) [and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it returned to its first state; it recommenced:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajaEotu EawodiY EalaY", "text_ar": "رَجَعْتُ عَوْدِى عَلَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoy^iY", "text_ar": "بَدْيِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I returned like as I had come."}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 164}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Sb ubi suprà.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "First, or former; preceding all others,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "preceding another;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albado'u badiYo'N", "text_ar": "البَدْءُ بَدِىْءٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbadiY'u", "text_ar": "البَدِىءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aw~alu", "text_ar": "الاَوَّلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, K.) Hence the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AifoEalohu baAdiY bado'K", "text_ar": "اِفْعَلْهُ بَادِى بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiY badiYo'K", "text_ar": "بَادِى بَدِىْءٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Do thou it the first thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the first of everything;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[accord. to different copies of the S;] the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAdY", "text_ar": "بادى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being quiescent, in the place of the accus. case, accord. to usage; and sometimes they omit the [altogether], on account of frequent use [of the phrase], as will be stated in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bdw", "text_ar": "بدو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S in the present art.,) saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiY badK", "text_ar": "بَادِى بَدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYbadiY", "text_ar": "بَادِىبَدِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bdw", "text_ar": "بدو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AifoEalohu bado'FA", "text_ar": "اِفْعَلْهُ بَدْءًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aw~ala bado'K", "text_ar": "اَوَّلَ بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Th, M, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'a bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدْءَ بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (CK,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badaA bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدَا بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiy^a", "text_ar": "بَادِيَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A'Obeyd, T, S, M, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYa badK", "text_ar": "بَادِىَ بَدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYo badFA", "text_ar": "بَادِىْ بَدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K, [in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYo badK", "text_ar": "بَادِىْ بَدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYo badFA", "text_ar": "بَادِىْ بَدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYo'K", "text_ar": "بَدِىْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAday^a", "text_ar": "بَادَيَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYo badaA", "text_ar": "بَادِىْ بَدَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYo'K", "text_ar": "بَدِىْءٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiy^a", "text_ar": "بَادِيَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A'Obeyd, T, S, M, CK,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiY~K", "text_ar": "بَدِىٍّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiy^a", "text_ar": "بَادِيَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is anomalous, (M,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYa bad~iYi", "text_ar": "بَادِىَ بَدِّىِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYo", "text_ar": "بَادِىْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiy~K", "text_ar": "بَدِيٍّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Fr, A'Obeyd, T, S, M,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiy^K", "text_ar": "بَدِيٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiy^a", "text_ar": "بَادِيَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, CK,) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYa badiy^K", "text_ar": "بَادِىَ بَدِيٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYo", "text_ar": "بَادِىْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K, TA,) the former word being the act. part. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYa", "text_ar": "بَدِىَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is of the dial. of the Ansár, as mentioned above, and the latter being indecl., with fet-h for its termination, (TA, [in the CK the latter word is written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'ap", "text_ar": "بَدْءَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (CK,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa badoA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ بَدْاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYo'K", "text_ar": "بَدِىْءٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYo'a", "text_ar": "بَدِىْءَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, CK,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'a *iY bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدْءَ ذِى بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Fr, T,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iY bado'K", "text_ar": "ذِى بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Fr, T, S, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa *iY badoA^apK", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ ذِى بَدْاَةٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iY badiYo'K", "text_ar": "ذِى بَدِىْءٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iy badaA='apa", "text_ar": "ذِي بَدَا=ءَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badaA^apa", "text_ar": "بَدَاَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bdA'p", "text_ar": "بداءة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as in the CK], (TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYo'a *iY badiYo'K", "text_ar": "بَدِىْءَ ذِى بَدِىْءٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K, TA, [in the CK the last word is written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'K", "text_ar": "بَدْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iY badiYo'K", "text_ar": "ذِى بَدِىْءٍ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badaA='api", "text_ar": "بَدَا=ءَةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Do thou it the first thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr, T, K;) so in a correct copy [of the K, and so I find in a MS. copy of the K and in the CK]: accord. to another copy,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the first of everything:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the first of first;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) thus in the L: (TA:) the words here put in the accus. case [literally or virtually] are so put [in some instances] as adverbial nouns; or, accord. to MF, they may be [in some instances] 