on,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "judgment;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as is implied in the A, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Say~uwrN", "text_ar": "صَيُّورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.:] hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~aA^oyi", "text_ar": "الرَّاْيِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEalahu fiY baAdiy^i", "text_ar": "فَعَلَهُ فِى بَادِيِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He did it at first thought,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]: (M:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~aA^oYi turiydu", "text_ar": "الرَّاْىِ تُرِيدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anota baAdiy^a", "text_ar": "اَنْتَ بَادِيَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ZulomanaA", "text_ar": "ظُلْمَنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlrA^Y", "text_ar": "الراى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mubotadaA^a", "text_ar": "مُبْتَدَاَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i.e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou at first thought,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "desirest to wrong us:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and one says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiYa AlrA^Y", "text_ar": "بَادِىَ الراى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", without; meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on the occasion of what appeared of opinion;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the first of what appeared thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the first opinion's presenting itself;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";] in which case, the phrase does not belong to this art. [but to art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bdw", "text_ar": "بدو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: it occurs in the Kur xi. 29: (M:) AA alone there read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAdiy^a", "text_ar": "بَادِيَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with; all the other readers pronounced it without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A chief,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lord,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who occupies the first place in chieftainship"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lordship:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a youth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "young man, whose judgment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "opinion, is deemed good, and who is consulted:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) or it signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an intelligent youth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "young man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buduwo'N", "text_ar": "بُدُوْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M.) A poet (namely, Ows Ibn-Maghrà Es-Saadee, TA) says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "vunoyaAnunaA A_ino A^ataAhumo kaAna badoA^ahumu\n                      \n                     \n                        wabadow^uhumo A_ino A^ataAnaA kiAna vunoyaAnaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Our second chief, if he came to them, would be their first chief; and their first chief, if he came to us, would be a second chief"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) ―         -b4-  Also, and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badoA^apN", "text_ar": "بَدْاَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A share,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a slaughtered camel: (S, K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "best share"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thereof: (T:) or the former word has the latter signification; and the latter word, the former signification: and the former signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a bone with the meat,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "flesh, that is on it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a joint;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mafoSilN", "text_ar": "مَفْصِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (AA, T, M;) and so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badFA", "text_ar": "بَدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "q.v.: (AA, T:) the pl. [of pauc.] of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bado'N", "text_ar": "بَدْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abodaA='N", "text_ar": "اَبْدَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K) and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buduwo'N", "text_ar": "بُدُوْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, K;) the former of which is the more common: (TA:) or this is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badFA", "text_ar": "بَدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (AA, T.) The shares abovementioned [as commonly divided for the game called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almayosir", "text_ar": "المَيْسِر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "q. v.] are ten; namely, the two haunches, the two thighs properly so called, the two thighs commonly so called (i. e. the tibiæ), the two shoulders, and the two arms; which last are the worst, because of the many veins [therein]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badiYo'N", "text_ar": "بَدِىْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["M", "K", "As", "TA", "S", "Msb", "L", "Mtr", "AZ", "Mgh", "T", "Sb", "Th", "CK", "Fr", "Lh", "AA"]}, {"entry_id": "n1953", "headword_ar": "بُدءٌ", "root": "bdA^", "bod